Prerequisites
=============

LibLunar-gtk requires Gtk+-2.16.x libraries.
PyGtk 2.16.x are required to enable python binding support.

Simple install procedure
========================

  $ tar -zxf liblunar-gtk-@LIBLUNAR_VERSION@.tar.gz              # unpack the sources
  $ cd liblunar-gtk-@LIBLUNAR_VERSION@                           # change to the toplevel directory
  $ ./configure                                 # run the `configure' script
  $ make                                        # build liblunar-gtk
  [ Become root if necessary ]
  $ sudo make install                           # install liblunar-gtk

